The d-beam energy was 300 keV and the intensity
was 5 mA. A sample transport system of six
pneumatic tubes provided irradiation positions giving
monochromatic neutrons of 13.4-14.9 MeV. Another tube
was put at -105 deg to check the symmetry of the
system. The irradiation positions was about 15 cm from
the tritium target. An additional tube set at -22.5
deg and at 1.5 cm distance was used when strong
